<div class="panel panel-primary" id="">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">MS Service at Sheffield Teaching Hospitals </h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>The department provides a comprehensive inpatient, outpatient, and day case service to people with multiple sclerosis and allied conditions such as Neuromyelitis Optica.</p>
    <p>We have a team of consultants interested in multiple sclerosis and one with a neurological disability interest. There is also an excellent team of MS Specialist nurses.</p>
    <p>The service is supported by excellent in-patient, day patient, diagnostic radiology and neurophysiology services. The team is also involved in patient and health professional education and highly active in research, both clinical trials and through links with basic science researchers.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="panel panel-primary" id="">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">Notes for Health Care Professionals</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>We are a centre for the MIST clinical trial. </p>
    <p>This is a worldwide trial of AHSCT compared to standard of care. Brief inclusion criteria are patients with relapsing remitting multiple sclerosis who have had continuing relapses despite the use of disease modifying therapy, with at least two clinical relapses requiring steroids treatment within the last year, or one relapse treated with steroids in the last year with an MRI scan of the brain showing a gadolinium enhancing lesion at least 3 months prior or after that relapse. </p>
    <p><a href="https://www.clinicaltrials.gov/ct2/show/NCT00273364" target="_blank">Full inclusion and exclusion criteria for the MIST clinical trial can be found here</a></p>
  </div>
</div>

